son cornelius & indonus van diest, which is accepted & shall bee
plased to your accompt. Jacobvan Herentals is to bee blamed for
his neglectinge the last convoije, butt itt seemes hee could not

Londen Jamuel blewilt
have yours of 23 past, with a bill of tl £100 a 34:2 att o br
charge of Joachin de sadelaer oft gand, which I have sent for acceptance
sayd sadelaer is a man, of vere good credit & reputacion, so that I doe not
in the least doubt of the punctuall payemend when accepted, there by
I Kknow the drawer, to bee avere habell man, so that that monney is as good
as in cash to my opinion, I shall provide the tykes you order & forward them
by the first opportunitie, whe here is the vessel of marten John son in loadinge
for londen, partes this week, if I can, shall endeavour to send hem with
him, & advise you what passes, whils t I rest
Londen Christoph Batt
Mij last to you was p. curt, then made bold to send your accompt, & to
dispose of the ballance which now am sorrie to have done, yett the bill beinge
payable to m Kent & comp, shall suffer no disgrace, because I have credit
by them, haveinge before mee yours of 26 past, with 2 bills toghether for £216:
14:5 en a 34 s which makes £369:6:7 en & the ballance due to me is
£369:11:4 et so that should differ 28 stivers, which I shall fiedeogeed if
you finde so to agree, shall be found good on your frst order if you please,
whilst I shall writte o of on my bovkes to agree with yours, pray excuse
my drawinge, t'was accompt, & for reason as in my last, which for the
futture shall not bee don more. I am sorrie, that your last 3 packes lye by
still, & that to be the reason, that you demand no goods from mee att present
I know you have a bast demand, & great trade, so that these may easeley
bee scould before, you can receave anney others packetts from mee, & is
now plentie, white well to be had, pray lett mee have part of your commissions, you
will foy de feare dealinge by mee, & sure as well, if not better served as by prr
furnese, itt beinge not your infrest to my opinion to imploy him, because
Leyden Hendrick Harmant
Ick hebbe geordonneert aen wonter segers van tilborgh aen ue te seynde
13 witte lakens, het fyn te voor swert dobbelstael, ende andere 2 tot
carmosijn vande alderschoonste buyn coleur dat can geverft ue oorden
soo haest ue die lakens becomt, soo laetse nat meden, ende schrijftmy de
numbers & lenghde, & verliest geenen tijt, om die claer te hebben ende wel
te doen, de carmosyne, sult gij laeten verven, by govaert velthuysen
gedaen synde naer tilborgh aen wonter segers wederseynden, ben waer
Eekn anders ordonneerde, naer groetenisse blijve.
